Scripts to generates a daily digest PDF in pocketmod booklet form to print out and enjoy.

See: http://www.pocketmod.com/

I'm slowly filling in the pages of the booklet. I'll add them here in the order they appear:

1. Last.fm event recommendations
2. Tube line and station status
3. Twitter updates
4. Newsgator RSS headlines
5. Google calendar + Weather
6. Flickr photo spread left
7. Flickr photo spread right
8. 

Required libs:
- pylast 0.3 branch (slightly modified â€” ask for details): http://code.google.com/p/pylast/ GPL
- simplejson: http://code.google.com/p/simplejson/ MIT
- BeautifulSoup: http://www.crummy.com/software/BeautifulSoup/ BSD
- feedparser: http://www.feedparser.org/ MIT
- gdata-python-client: http://code.google.com/p/gdata-python-client/ Apache
- flickrapi: http://stuvel.eu/projects/flickrapi  Python

Bundled libs:
- Some Django utils: http://www.djangoproject.com/ (BSD)
- ReportLab: http://www.reportlab.org/ (BSD)

You'll also need a settings module which defines these globals:
GMAPS_KEY
LASTFM_KEY
LASTFM_SECRET
LASTFM_SESSION
TWITTER_USERNAME
TWITTER_PASSWORD
TWITTER_USERID
NEWSGATOR_KEY
NEWSGATOR_USERNAME
NEWSGATOR_PASSWORD
NEWSGATOR_LOCATIONID
GCAL_USERNAME
GCAL_PASSWORD
GCAL_CALENDARS e.g. {'calendar id': ('display name': 'hexcolor')}
BBC_WEATHER_LOCATION e.g. 4581 in http://www.bbc.co.uk/weather/5day.shtml?world=4581
MET_WEATHER_REGION e.g. 'se' in http://www.metoffice.gov.uk/weather/uk/se/se_forecast_weather.html
MET_WEATHER_REGION_FULL e.g. London & South East England as seen at above URL
FLICKR_KEY
FLICKR_SECRET

APIs:
- Google Static Maps: http://code.google.com/apis/maps/documentation/staticmaps/
- Last.fm: http://www.last.fm/api
- Twitter: http://apiwiki.twitter.com/
- Newsgator: http://www.newsgator.com/ngs/api/
- Google Calendar: http://code.google.com/apis/calendar/
- Flickr: http://www.flickr.com/services/api/

RSS:
- BBC Weather: http://news.bbc.co.uk/weather/hi/about/newsid_7788000/7788189.stm
- Met Office warnings and advisories: http://www.metoffice.gov.uk/weather/uk/rss/help.html

Screen Scraping:
- TFL: http://www.tfl.gov.uk/